        <h1 class="heading-section">How to make a new Visa</h1>
        <p>
            A Vietnamese visa, which is a kind of travel document granted by Vietnamese competent authorities, is a permission to travel to Vietnam.<br />
            At the moment, there are up to 3 ways to get a Vietnam visa:<br />
            <ul>
                <li>On-arrival BUT a visa approval letter must be gained before arrival.</li>
                <li>At the Embassy or consulate;</li>
                <li>and e-visa (available for 1-month single entry, and granted for 80 countries).</li>
            </ul>
            The types of Vietnam visa consists of Tourist visa (DL):<br />
            <ul>
                <li>Business visa (DN1, DN2)</li>
                <li>Investor Visa (DT1, DT2, DT3, DT4)</li>
                <li>Working visa (LD1 – LD2, LV1 - LV2) working with Vietnam authorities/parties</li>
                <li>TT visa Dependents of LV1, LV2, LS, DT1, DT2, DT3, NN1, NN2, DH, PV1, LD1-LD2 visa holders, or foreigners that are parents, spouse, children of Vietnamese citizens. Maximum of 12 months</li>
                <li>EVisa(EV) Electronic visa  Maximum 30 days</li>
                <li>VR  Family visits, other purposes  Maximum of 6 months</li>
                <li>Diplomatic visa (NG)</li>
                <li>Student/internship visa (DH)</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
